The paper deals with image inpainting using GAN-based models, which is a topic related to computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves using local intrinsic dimensionality (LID) to measure alignment between data submanifolds, which is a technique that falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses improving structural consistency and textural details, which are aspects of graphics (cs.GR) and multimedia (cs.MM).
